Greatest Songs of the 1940s spotlights 33 hits released in that decade 
including Billie Holiday's "God Bless the Child," Glenn Miller's "Chattanooga 
Choo Choo," the Andrews Sisters' "Don't Sit Under the Apple Tree (With 
Anyone Else But Me)," and Bing Crosby's "Ac-Cent-Tchu-Ate the Positive." 
This is an inexpensive way to collect these songs in one package.

AAO Music / United Audio Entertainment #UMMC 63312)
